    A collection that contains a subset of items that are a part of a larger collection. The items within a partial collection begin at an offset within the full collection and end at a specified limit. Note that the actual size of a partial collection may be less than its limit since the limit only specifies the maximum size. For example, if there's a full collection with a size of 3, then a partial collection with offset 0 and limit 3 would be equal to a partial collection with offset 0 and limit 100.
